{
  "stem": "24346.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Because that was April the 15th, a Monday or a Sunday.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I recall her, but that was that time, and war was still on.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "So soldiers, American, used to come in.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "We had no electricity.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "However, we got some candles-- maybe from the office, because when I came, it was already there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "So we got some candles and we lit up candles to see in the evening a little light.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A guy comes in, knock at the door, comes in.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And you couldn't see from the table, short of the candles by the door, who's coming in.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He comes in-- [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Shut off, because German planes are still in the air.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we can't have lights on.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And to me, his German sounded like Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I said to that Volvek, what his brother was looking for him, I say, he sounds like Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Let's ask him.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This guy, the soldier, heard the word Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He came over-- you speak Yiddish?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I said, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now he spoke in Jewish and said, juden?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I said, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He said, ich bin Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Ich bin von der Bronx, New York.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My tateh, my father is a cantor and a mohel.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "My namen is Walter Schrader.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So I said, I can  never forget this name-- the first American Jewish guy.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He said, tomorrow, I'll come over.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I'll bring you some goodies, some chewing gum, some chocolate, from down at PX.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Sure enough, the next day, he knew already he had here a dozen or so, 15 Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He came in with that backpack, chewing gum and chocolate-- all real stuff that we couldn't imagine that will ever see in our lives.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "However, this guy brought it over-- Walter Schrader.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
